obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38567)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38567&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hindu Marriage Act, 1955.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*, and applies also to`
  line `Hindus domiciled in the territories to which this Act extends who are outside the said territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38568)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38568&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act applies`
  line
  line `(a) to any person who is a Hindu by religion in any of its forms or developments, including a`
  line `Virashaiva, a Lingayat or a follower of the Brahmo, Prarthana or Arya Samaj,`
  line
  line `(b) to any person who is a Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh by religion, and`
  line
  line `(c) to any other person domiciled in the territories to which this Act extends who is not a Muslim,`
  line `Christian, Parsi or Jew by religion, unless it is proved that any such person would not have been`
  line `governed by the Hindu law or by any custom or usage as part of that law in respect of any of the`
  line `matters dealt with herein if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.The following persons are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or Sikhs by religion, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line
  line `(a) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, both of whose parents are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or`
  line `Sikhs by religion;`
  line
  line `(b) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, one of whose parents is a Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh`
  line `by religion and who is brought up as a member of the tribe, community, group or family to which`
  line `such parent belongs or belonged; and`
  line
  line `(c) any person who is a convert or re-convert to the Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh religion.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), nothing contained in this Act shall apply`
  line `to the members of any Scheduled tribe within the meaning of clause (25) of article 366 of the Constitution`
  line `unless the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(3) The expression "Hindu" in any portion of this Act shall be construed as if it included a person`
  line `who, though not a Hindu by religion, is, nevertheless, a person to whom this Act applies by virtue of the`
  line `provisions contained in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38569)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38569&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) the expressions "custom" and "usage" signify any rule which, having been continuously and`
  line `uniformly observed for a long time, has obtained the force of law among Hindus in any local area,`
  line `tribe, community, group or family:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rule is certain and not unreasonable or opposed to public policy; and`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a rule applicable only to a family it has not been discontinued`
  line `by the family;`
  line
  line `(b) "district court" means, in any area for which there is a city civil court, that court, and in any`
  line `other area the principal civil court of original jurisdiction, and includes any other civil court which may be specified by the State Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, as having`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of the matters dealt with in this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "full blood" and "half blood"— two persons are said to be related to each other by full blood`
  line `when they are descended from a common ancestor by the same wife and by half blood when they are`
  line `descended from a common ancestor but by different wives;`
  line
  line `(d) "uterine blood"—two persons are said to be related to each other by uterine blood when they`
  line `are descended from a common ancestress but by different husbands;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In clauses (c) and (d), "ancestor" includes the father and "ancestress" the mother;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) (i) "sapinda relationship" with reference to any person extends as far as the third generation`
  line `(inclusive) in the line of ascent through the mother, and the fifth (inclusive) in the line of ascent`
  line `through the father, the line being traced upwards in each case from the person concerned, who is to`
  line `be counted as the first generation;`
  line
  line `(ii) two persons are said to be sapindas of each other if one is a lineal ascendant of the`
  line `other within the limits of sapinda relationship, or if they have a common lineal ascendant who is`
  line `within the limits of sapinda relationship with reference to each of them;`
  line
  line `(g) "degrees of prohibited relationship"two persons are said to be within the "degrees of`
  line `prohibited relationship"`
  line
  line `(i) if one is a lineal ascendant of the other; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if one was the wife or husband of a lineal ascendant or descendant of the other; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if one was the wife of the brother or of the father's or mother's brother or of the`
  line `grandfather's or grandmother's brother of the other; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if the two are brother and sister, uncle and niece, aunt and nephew, or children of brother`
  line `and sister or of two brothers or of two sisters;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of clauses (f) and (g), relationship includes—`
  line
  line `(i) relationship by half or uterine blood as well as by full blood;`
  line
  line `(ii) illegitimate blood relationship as well as legitimate;`
  line
  line `(iii) relationship by adoption as well as by blood;`
  line
  line `and all terms of relationship in those clauses shall be construed accordingly`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38570)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Overriding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38570&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) any text rule or interpretation of Hindu law or any custom or usage as part of that law in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to have effect with respect to any`
  line `matter for which provision is made in this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any other law in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to have`
  line `effect in so far as it is inconsistent with any of the provisions contained in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38571)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conditions for a Hindu marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38571&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A marriage may be solemnized between any two Hindus, if`
  line `the following conditions are fulfilled, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) neither party has a spouse living at the time of the marriage;`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) at the time of the marriage, neither party`
  line
  line `(a) is incapable of giving a valid consent to it in consequence of unsoundness of mind; or`
  line
  line `(b) though capable of giving a valid consent, has been suffering from mental disorder of such`
  line `a kind or to such an extent as to be unfit for marriage and the procreation of children; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been subject to recurrent attacks of insanity ^2`
  line ***];
  line
  line `(iii) the bridegroom has completed the age of ^3[twenty-one years] and the bride, the age`
  line `of ^4[eighteen years] at the time of the marriage;`
  line
  line `(iv) the parties are not within the degrees of prohibited relationship unless the custom or usage`
  line `governing each of them permits of a marriage between the two;`
  line
  line `(v) the parties are not sapindas of each other, unless the custom or usage governing each of them`
  line `permits of a marriage between the two;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 2, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. The words or epilepsy omitted by Act 39 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and Schedule for elighteen years (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6 and Schedule, ibid., for fifteen years (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line `5. Clause (vi) omitted by s. 6 and Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
