  string
  line `[Guardianship in marriage.Omitted by the Child Marriage Restraint (Amendment) Act, 1978,`
  line `(2 of 1978), s. 6 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38573)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Ceremonies for a Hindu marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38573&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Hindu marriage may be solemnized in accordance`
  line `with the customary rites and ceremonies of either party thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such rites and ceremonies include the Saptapadi (that is, the taking of seven steps by the`
  line `bridegroom and the bride jointly before the sacred fire), the marriage becomes complete and binding`
  line `when the seventh step is taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38574)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Registration of Hindu marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38574&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of facilitating the proof of Hindu`
  line `marriages, the State Government may make rules providing that the parties to any such marriage may`
  line `have the particulars relating to their marriage entered in such manner and subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed in a Hindu Marriage Register kept for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government may, if it is of`
  line `opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do, provide that the entering of the particulars referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be compulsory in the State or in any part thereof, whether in all cases or in such`
  line `cases as may be specified, and where any such direction has been issued, any person contravening any`
  line `rule made in this behalf shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be laid before the State Legislature, as soon as may be,`
  line `after they are made.`
  line
  line `(4) The Hindu Marriage Register shall at all reasonable times be open for inspection, and shall be`
  line `admissible as evidence of the statements therein contained and certified extracts therefrom shall, on`
  line `application, be given by the Registrar on payment to him of the prescribed fee.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the validity of any Hindu marriage shall in no`
  line `way be affected by the omission to make the entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38575)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Restitution of conjugal right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38575&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `** * When either the husband or the wife has, without reasonable`
  line `excuse, withdrawn from the society of the other, the aggrieved party may apply, by petition to the district`
  line `court, for restitution of conjugal rights and the court, on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made`
  line `in such petition and that there is no legal ground why the application should not be granted, may decree`
  line `restitution of conjugal rights accordingly.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.—Where a question arises whether there has been reasonable excuse for withdrawal`
  line `from the society, the burden of proving reasonable excuse shall be on the person who has withdrawn from`
  line `the society.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure (1) omitted by Act 68 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38576)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Judicial separation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38576&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Either party to a marriage, whether solemnised before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, may present a petition praying for a decree for judicial separation on any of`
  line `the grounds specified in sub-section (1) of section 13, and in the case of a wife also on any of the grounds`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) thereof, as grounds on which a petition for divorce might have been`
  line presented.]
  line
  line `(2) Where a decree for judicial separation has been passed, it shall no longer be obligatory for the`
  line `petitioner to cohabit with the respondent, but the court may, on the application by petition of either party`
  line `and on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made in such petition, rescind the decree if it`
  line `considers it just and reasonable to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38577)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Void marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38577&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any marriage solemnised after the commencement of this Act shall be null`
  line `and void and may, on a petition presented by either party thereto ^1[against the other party], be so declared`
  line `by a decree of nullity if it contravenes any one of the conditions specified in clauses (i), (iv) and (v) of`
  line `section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38578)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Voidable marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38578&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any marriage solemnised, whether before or after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, shall be voidable and may be annulled by a decree of nullity on any of the following grounds,`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `^1[(a) that the marriage has not been consummated owing to the imporence of the respondent; or]`
  line
  line `(b) that the marriage is in contravention of the condition specified in clause (ii) of section 5; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the consent of the petitioner, or where the consent of the guardian in marriage of the`
  line `petitioner ^2[was required under section 5 as it stood immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Child Marriage Restraint (Amendment) Act, 1978 (2 of 1978)], the consent of such guardian was`
  line `obtained by force ^3[or by fraud as to the nature of the ceremony or as to any material fact or`
  line `circumstances concerning the respondent]; or`
  line
  line `(d) that the respondent was at the time of the marriage pregnant by some person other than the`
  line petitioner.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no petition for annulling a marriage`
  line
  line `(a) on the ground specified in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be entertained if`
  line
  line `(i) the petition is presented more than one year after the force had ceased to operate or, as the`
  line `case may be, the fraud had been discovered; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the petitioner has, with his or her full consent, lived with the other party to the marriage as`
  line `husband or wife after the force had ceased to operate or, as the case may be, the fraud had been`
  line discovered;
  line
  line `(b) on the ground specified in clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be entertained unless the court is`
  line satisfied
  line
  line `(i) that the petitioner was at the time of the marriage ignorant of the facts alleged;`
  line
  line `(ii) that proceedings have been instituted in the case of a marriage solemnised before the`
  line `commencement of this Act within one year of such commencement and in the case of marriages`
  line `solemnised after such commencement within one year from the date of the marriage; and`
  line
  line `(iii) that marital intercourse with the consent of the petitioner has not taken place since the`
  line `discovery by the petitioner of the existence of ^4[the said ground].`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and Schedule, for is required under section 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 6, for or fraud (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for the grounds for a decree (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38579)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Divorce.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38579&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any marriage solemnized, whether before or after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `may, on a petition presented by either the husband or the wife, be dissolved by a decree of divorce on the`
  line `ground that the other party--`
  line
  line `^1[(i) has, after the solemnization of the marriage, had voluntary sexual intercourse with any`
  line `person other than his or her spouse; or`
  line
  line `(ia) has, after the solemnization of the marriage, treated the petitioner with cruelty; or`
  line
  line `(ib) has deserted the petitioner for a continuous period of not less than two years immediately`
  line `preceding the presentation of the petition; or]`
  line
  line `(ii) has ceased to be a Hindu by conversion to another religion; or`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) has been incurably of unsound mind, or has been suffering continuously or intermittently`
  line `from mental disorder of such a kind and to such an extent that the petitioner cannot reasonably be`
  line `expected to live with the respondent.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression mental disorder means mental illness, arrested or incomplete`
  line `development of mind, psychopathic disorder or any other disorder or disability of mind and`
  line `includes schizophrenia;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression psychopathic disorder means a persistent disorder or disability of mind`
  line `(whether or not including subnormality of intelligence) which results in abnormally aggressive`
  line `or seriously irresponsible conduct on the part of the other party, and whether or not it requires or`
  line `is susceptible to medical treatment; or]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) has ^3* * * been suffering from venereal disease in a communicable form; or`
  line
  line `(vi) has renounced the world by entering any religious order; or`
  line
  line `(vii) has not been heard of as being alive for a period of seven years or more by those persons`
  line `who would naturally have heard of it, had that party been alive; ^4***`
  line
  line `^5*** *`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation.In this sub-section, the expression desertion means the desertion of the`
  line `petitioner by the other party to the marriage without reasonable cause and without the consent or`
  line `against the wish of such party, and includes the wilful neglect of the petitioner by the other party to the`
  line `marriage, and its grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall be construed accordingly.]`
  line
  line `^7[(1A) Either party to a marriage, whether solemnized before or after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `may also present a petition for the dissolution of the marriage by a decree of divorce on the ground`
  line
  line `(i) that there has been no resumption of cohabitation as between the parties to the marriage for a`
  line `period of ^8[one year] or upwards after the passing of a decree for judicial separation in a proceeding`
  line `to which they were parties; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that there has been no restitution of conjugal rights as between the parties to the marriage for a`
  line `period of ^8[one year] or upwards after the passing of a decree for restitution of conjugal rights in a`
  line `proceeding to which they were parties.]`
  line
  line `(2) A wife may also present a petition for the dissolution of her marriage by a decree of divorce on`
  line `the ground,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of any marriage solemnized before the commencement of this Act, that the husband`
  line `had married again before such commencement or that any other wife of the husband married before`
  line `such commencement was alive at the time of the solemnization of the marriage of the petitioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in either case the other wife is alive at the time of the presentation of the petition; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that the husband has, since the solemnization of the marriage, been guilty of rape, sodomy or`
  line `^9[bestiality; or]`
  line
  line `^10[(iii) that in a suit under section 18 of the Hindu Adoptions and Maintenance Act, 1956`
  line `(78 of 1956), or in a proceeding under section 125 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974) (or under the corresponding section 488 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898`
  line `(5 of 1898), a decree or order, as the case may be, has been passed against the husband awarding`
  line `maintenance to the wife notwithstanding that she was living apart and that since the passing of such`
  line `decree or order, cohabitation between the parties has not been resumed for one year or upwards;`
  line
  line `(iv) that her marriage (whether consummated or not) was solemnized before she attained the age`
  line `of fifteen years and she has repudiated the marriage after attaining that age but before attaining the`
  line `age of eighteen years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.This clause applies whether the marriage was solemnized before or after the`
  line `commencement of the Marriage Laws (Amendment) Act, 1976 (68 of 1976).]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13 of Act XXV of 1955.--In sub-section (1) of section 13 of the Hindu Marriage`
  line `Act, 1955,--`
  line
  line `(a) after clause (i) the following new cause shall be inserted and shall be deemed always to have`
  line `been inserted;`
  line
  line `"(i-a) has persistently or repeatedly treated the petitioner with such cruelty as to cause a`
  line `reasonable apprehension in the mind of the petitioner that it will be harmful or injurious for the`
  line `petitioner to live with the other party ;or", and`
  line
  line `(b) for clause (vii), the following clause shall be substituted and shall be deemed always to have`
  line `been substituted;`
  line
  line `"(viii) has not resumed cohabitation after the passing of a decree for judicial separation against`
  line `that party and--`
  line
  line `(a) a period of two years has elapsed since the passing of such decree, or`
  line
  line `(b) the case is one of exceptional hardship to the petitioner or of exceptional depravity on the part`
  line `of the other party; or".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XIII of 1962, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 7, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clause (iii) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (iv) omitted by Act 6 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The word or omitted by Act 44 of 1964, s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-12-1964).`
  line
  line `5. Clauses (viii) and (ix) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-12-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 7 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 44 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-12-1964).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 7, for two years (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 7, for bestiality (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-2976).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (38580)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 14
  title `Alternate relief in divorce proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 8 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38580&sectionno=13A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Alternate relief in divorce proceedings.—In any proceeding under this Act, on a petition for`
  line `dissolution of marriage by a decree of divorce, except in so far as the petition is founded on the grounds`
  line `mentioned in clauses (ii), (vi) and (vii) of sub-section (1) of section 13, the court may, if it considers it just`
  line `so to do having regard to the circumstances of the case, pass instead a decree for judicial separation.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (38581)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 15
  title `Divorce by mutual consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38581&sectionno=13B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act a petition for dissolution`
  line `of marriage by a decree of divorce may be presented to the district court by both the parties to a marriage`
  line `together, whether such marriage was solemnized before or after the commencement of the Marriage Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1976 (68 of 1976), on the ground that they have been living separately for a period of`
  line `one year or more, that they have not been able to live together and that they have mutually agreed that the`
  line `marriage should be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) On the motion of both the parties made not earlier than six months after the date of the`
  line `presentation of the petition referred to in sub-section (1) and not later than eighteen months after the said`
  line `date, if the petition is not withdrawn in the meantime, the court shall, on being satisfied, after hearing the`
  line `parties and after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, that a marriage has been solemnized and that the`
  line `averments in the petition are true, pass a decree of divorce declaring the marriage to be dissolved with`
  line `effect from the date of the decree.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38582)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `No petition for divorce to be presented within one year of marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38582&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, it shall not be competent for any court to entertain any petition for`
  line `dissolution of a marriage by a decree of divorce, ^1[unless at the date of the presentation of the petition one`
  line `one year has elapsed] since the date of the marriage:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, upon application made to it in accordance with such rules as may be`
  line `made by the High Court in that behalf, allow a petition to be presented ^1[before one year has elapsed]`
  line `since the date of the marriage on the ground that the case is one of exceptional hardship to the petitioner`
  line `or of exceptional depravity on the part of the respondent, but if it appears to the court at the hearing of the`
  line `petition that the petitioner obtained leave to present the petition by any misrepresentation or concealment`
  line `of the nature of the case, the court may, if it pronounces a decree, do so subject to the condition that the decree shall not have effect until after the ^2[expiry of one year] from the date of the marriage or may`
  line `dismiss the petition without prejudice to any petition which may be brought after ^3[expiration of the said one year] upon the same or substantially the same facts as those alleged in support of the petition`
  line `so dismissed.`
  line
  line `(2) In disposing of any application under this section for leave to present a petition for divorce before`
  line `the ^4[expiration of one year] from the date of the marriage, the court shall have regard to the interests of`
  line `any children of the marriage and to the question whether there is a reasonable probability of a`
  line `reconciliation between the parties before the expiration of the ^5[said one year].`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 9, for "expiry of three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 9, for "expiration of the said one year" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 9, for "expiry of three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 9, for "said three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38583)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Divorced persons when may marry again.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Proviso omitted by Act 68 of 1976, s.10 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38583&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When a marriage has been dissolved by a decree of`
  line `divorce and either there is no right of appeal against the decree or, if there is such a right of appeal, the`
  line `time for appealing has expired without an appeal having been presented, or an appeal has been presented`
  line `but has been dismissed, it shall be lawful for either party to the marriage to marry again.`
  line
  line ^1*****
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38584)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Legitimacy of children of void and voidable marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 11, for section16 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38584&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Legitimacy of children of void and voidable marriages.--(1) Notwithstanding that a marriage`
  line `marriage is null and void under section 11, any child of such marriage who would have been legitimate if`
  line `the marriage had been valid, shall be legitimate, whether such child is born before or after the`
  line `commencement of the Marriage Laws (Amendment) Act, 1976 (68 of 1976), and whether or not a decree`
  line `of nullity is granted in respect of that marriage under this Act and whether or not the marriage is held to`
  line `be void otherwise than on a petition under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a decree of nullity is granted in respect of a voidable marriage under section 12, any child`
  line `begotten or conceived before the decree is made, who would have been the legitimate child of the parties`
  line `to the marriage if at the date of the decree it had been dissolved instead of being annulled, shall be`
  line `deemed to be their legitimate child notwithstanding the decree of nullity.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be construed as conferring upon any`
  line `child of a marriage which is null and void or which is annulled by a decree of nullity under section 12,`
  line `any rights in or to the property of any person, other than the parents, in any case where, but for the`
  line `passing of this Act, such child would have been incapable of possessing or acquiring any such rights by`
  line `reason of his not being the legitimate child of his parents.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38585)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Punishment of bigamy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38585&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any marriage between two Hindus solemnized after the`
  line `commencement of this Act is void if at the date of such marriage either party had a husband or wife`
  line `living; and the provisions of sections 494 and 495 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860 (45 of 1860), shall`
  line `apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38586)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Punishment for contravention of certain other conditions for a Hindu marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38586&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `person who procures a marriage of himself or herself to be solemnized under this Act in contravention of`
  line `the conditions specified in clauses (iii), (iv), ^1[and (v)] of section 5 shall be punishable`
  line
  line `^2[(a) in the case of contravention of the condition specified in clause (iii) of section 5, with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a contravention of the condition specified in clause (iv) or clause (v) of`
  line `section 5, with simpleimprisonment which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees, or with both; ^3* * *`
  line
  line ^4*****
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and Schedule, for (v) and (vi) (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 2007, s. 20 (w.e.f. 30-10-2007).`
  line `3. The word and omitted by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line `4. Clause (c) omitted by Act 2 of 1987, s. 6 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38587)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Court to which petition shall be presented.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38587&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Court to which petition shall be presented.—Every petition under this Act shall be presented`
  line `to the District Court within the local limits of whose ordinary original civil jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `(i) the marriage was solemnized, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the respondent, at the time of the presentation of the petition, resides, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the parties to the marriage last resided together, or`
  line
  line `^2[(iiia) in case the wife is the petitioner, where she is residing on the date of presentation of the`
  line `petition; or]`
  line
  line `(iv) the petitioner is residing at the time of the presentation of the petition, in a case where the`
  line `respondent is at that time, residing outside the territories to which this Act extends, or has not been`
  line `heard of as being alive for a period of seven years or more by those persons who would naturally have`
  line `heard of him if he were alive.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 12, for s. 19 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 50 of 2003, s. 4 (w.e.f. 23-12-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38588)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Contents and verification of petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 13, for "and shall also State" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38588&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every petition presented under this Act shall state`
  line `as distinctly as the nature of the case permits the facts on which the claim to relief is founded ^1[and,`
  line `except in a petition under section 11, shall also state] that there is no collusion between the petitioner and`
  line `the other party to the marriage.`
  line
  line `(2) The statements contained in every petition under this Act shall be verified by the petitioner or`
  line `some other competent person in the manner required by law for the verification of plaints, and may, at the`
  line `hearing, be referred to as evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38589)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Application of Act 5 of 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38589&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act and to such`
  line `rules as the High Court may make in this behalf, all proceedings under this Act shall be regulated, as far`
  line `as may be, by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (38590)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to transfer petitions in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 14 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38590&sectionno=21A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Power to transfer petitions in certain cases.—`
  line `(1) Where—`
  line
  line `(a) a petition under this Act has been presented to a district court having jurisdiction by a party to`
  line `a marriage praying for a decree for judicial separation under section 10 or for a decree of divorce`
  line `under section 13, and`
  line
  line `(b) another petition under this Act has been presented thereafter by the other party to the marriage`
  line `praying for a decree for judicial separation under section 10 or for a decree of divorce under section`
  line `13 on any ground, whether in the same district court or in a different district court, in the same State`
  line `or in a different State,`
  line
  line `the petitions shall be dealt with as specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) In a case where sub-section (1) applies,`
  line
  line `(a) if the petitions are presented to the same district court, both the petitions shall be tried and`
  line `heard together by that district court;`
  line
  line `(b) if the petitions are presented to different district courts, the petition presented later shall be`
  line `transferred to the district court in which the earlier petition was presented and both the petitions shall`
  line `be heard and disposed of together by the district court in which the earlier petition was presented.`
  line
  line `(3) In a case where clause (b) of sub-section (2) applies, the court or the Government, as the case may`
  line `be, competent under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to transfer any suit or proceeding`
  line `from the district court in which the later petition has been presented to the district court in which the`
  line `earlier petition is pending, shall exercise its powers to transfer such later petition as if it had been`
  line `empowered so to do under the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b:
  sectionId (38591)
  sectionNo 21B
  orderNo 25
  title `Special provision relating to trial and disposal of petitions under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38591&sectionno=21B&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The trial of a`
  line `petition under this Act shall, so far as is practicable consistently with the interests of justice in respect of`
  line `the trial, be continued from day to day until its conclusion unless the court finds the adjournment of the`
  line `trial beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be recorded.`
  line
  line `(2) Every petition under this Act shall be tried as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be`
  line `made to conclude the trial within six months from the date of service of notice of the petition on the`
  line respondent.
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this Act shall be heard as expeditiously as possible, and endeavour shall be`
  line `made to conclude the hearing within three months from the date of service of notice of appeal on the`
  line respondent.
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21_c:
  sectionId (38592)
  sectionNo 21C
  orderNo 26
  title `Documentary evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38592&sectionno=21C&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any enactment to the contrary, no`
  line `document shall be inadmissible in evidence in any proceeding at the trial of a petition under this Act on`
  line `the ground that it is not duly stamped or registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38593)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Proceedings to be in camera and may not be printed or published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 15, for s. 22 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38593&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Proceedings to be in camera and may not be printed or published.—(1) Every proceeding`
  line `under this Act shall be conducted in camera and it shall not be lawful for any person to print or publish`
  line `any matter in relation to any such proceeding except a judgment of the High Court or of the Supreme`
  line `Court printed or published with the previous permission of the court.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person prints or publishes any matter in contravention of the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38594)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Decree in proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38594&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceeding under this Act, whether defended or not, if the`
  line `court is satisfied that`
  line
  line `(a) any of the grounds for granting relief exists and the petitioner ^1[except in cases where the`
  line `relief is sought by him on the ground specified in sub-clause (a), sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (c) of`
  line `clause (ii) of section 5] is not in any way taking advantage of his or her own wrong or disability for`
  line `the purpose of such relief, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the ground of the petition is the ground specified ^2* * * in clause (i) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 13, the petitioner has not in any manner been accessory to or connived at or condoned the`
  line `act or acts complained of, or where the ground of the petition is cruelty the petitioner has not in any`
  line `manner condoned the cruelty, and`
  line
  line `^1[(bb) when a divorce is sought on the ground of mutual consent, such consent has not been`
  line `obtained by force, fraud or undue influence, and]`
  line
  line `(c)^3[the petition (not being a petition presented under section 11)] is not presented or prosecuted`
  line `in collusion with the respondent, and`
  line
  line `(d) there has not been any unnecessary or improper delay in instituting the proceeding, and`
  line
  line `(e) there is no other legal ground why relief should not be granted, then, and in such a case, but`
  line `not otherwise, the court shall decree such relief accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Before proceeding to grant any relief under this Act, it shall be the duty of the court in the first`
  line `instance, in every case where it is possible so to do consistently with the nature and circumstances of the`
  line `case, to make every endeavour to bring about reconciliation between the parties:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any proceeding wherein relief is`
  line `sought on any of the grounds specified in clause (ii), clause (iii), clause (iv), clause (v), clause (vi) or`
  line `clause (vii) of sub-section (1) of section 13.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) For the purpose of aiding the court in bringing about such reconciliation, the court may, if the`
  line `parties so desire or if the court thinks it just and proper so to do, adjourn the proceedings for a reasonable`
  line `period not exceeding fifteen days and refer the matter to any person named by the parties in this behalf or`
  line `to any person nominated by the court if the parties fail to name any person, with directions to report to the`
  line `court as to whether reconciliation can be and has been, effected and the court shall in disposing of the`
  line `proceeding have due regard to the report.`
  line
  line `(4) In every case where a marriage is dissolved by a decree of divorce, the court passing the decree`
  line `shall give a copy thereof free of cost to each of the parties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. The words, bracket, letter of figure in clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 10 or omitted by s. 16, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for the petition (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `4. Added by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 16 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976)`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (38595)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 29
  title `Relief for respondent in divorce and other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by Act 68 of 1976, s. 17, (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38595&sectionno=23A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[In any proceeding for divorce or`
  line `judicial separation or restitution of conjugal rights, the respondent may not only oppose the relief sought`
  line `on the ground of petitioners adultery, cruelty or desertion, but also make a counter-claim for any relief`
  line `under this Act on that ground; and if the petitioners adultery, cruelty or desertion is proved, the court`
  line `may give to the respondent any relief under this Act to which he or she would have been entitled if he or`
  line `she had presented a petition seeking such relief on that ground.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38596)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 30
  title `Maintenance pendente lite and expenses of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 8 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38596&sectionno=24&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where in any proceeding under this`
  line `Act it appears to the court that either the wife or the husband, as the case may be, has no independent`
  line `income sufficient for her or his support and the necessary expenses of the proceeding, it may, on the`
  line `application of the wife or the husband, order the respondent to pay to the petitioner the expenses of the`
  line `proceeding, and monthly during the proceeding such sum as, having regard to the petitioners own`
  line `income and the income of the respondent, it may seem to the court to be reasonable.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the application for the payment of the expenses of the proceeding and such monthly`
  line `sum during the proceeding, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days from the date of`
  line `service of notice on the wife or the husband, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38597)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 31
  title `Permanent alimony and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38597&sectionno=25&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any court exercising jurisdiction under this Act`
  line `may, at the time of passing any decree or at any time subsequent thereto, on application made to it for the`
  line `purpose by either the wife or the husband, as the case may be, order that the respondent shall ^1*** pay to`
  line `the applicant for her or his maintenance and support such gross sum or such monthly or periodical sum`
  line `for a term not exceeding the life of the applicant as, having regard to the respondents own income and`
  line `other property, if any, the income and other property of the applicant ^2[the conduct of the parties and other`
  line `circumstances of the case], it may seem to the court to be just, and any such payment may be secured, if`
  line `necessary, by a charge on the immovable property of the respondent.`
  line
  line `(2) If the court is satisfied that there is a change in the circumstances of either party at any time after`
  line `it has made an order under sub-section (1), it may, at the instance of either party, vary, modify or rescind`
  line `any such order in such manner as the court may deem just.`
  line
  line `(3) If the court is satisfied that the party in whose favour an order has been made under this section`
  line `has re-married or, if such party is the wife, that she has not remained chaste, or, if such party is the`
  line `husband, that he has had sexual intercourse with any woman outside wedlock, ^3[it may at the instance of`
  line `the other party vary, modify or rescind any such order in such manner as the court may deem just.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words while the applicant remains unmarried omitted by Act 68 of 1976, s. 18 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for certain words. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for it shall rescind the order (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38598)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 32
  title `Custody of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 9 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38598&sectionno=26&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, the court may, from time to time, pass`
  line `such interim orders and make such provisions in the decree as it may deem just and proper with respect to`
  line `the custody, maintenance and education of minor children, consistently with their wishes, wherever`
  line `possible, and may, after the decree, upon application by petition for the purpose, make from time to time,`
  line `all such orders and provisions with respect to the custody, maintenance and education of such children as`
  line `might have been made by such decree or interim orders in case the proceeding for obtaining such decree`
  line `were still pending, and the court may also from time to time revoke, suspend or vary any such orders and`
  line `provisions previously made:`
  line
  line `^1Provided that the application with respect to the maintenance and education of the minor children,`
  line `pending the proceeding for obtaining such decree, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty`
  line `days from the date of service of notice on the respondent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38599)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 33
  title `Disposal of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38599&sectionno=27&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, the court may make such provisions in`
  line `the decree as it deems just and proper with respect to any property presented, at or about the time of`
  line `marriage, which may belong jointly to both the husband and the wife.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38600)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 34
  title `Appeals from decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38600&sectionno=28&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) All decrees made by the court in any proceeding under`
  line `this Act shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be appealable as decrees of the court made in`
  line `the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction, and every such appeal shall lie to the court to which appeals`
  line `ordinarily lie from the decisions of the court given in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Orders made by the court in any proceeding under this Act under section 25 or section 26 shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be appealable if they are not interim orders, and every such`
  line `appeal shall lie to the court to which appeals ordinarily lie from the decisions of the court given in`
  line `exercise of its original civil jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be no appeal under this section on the subject of costs only.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a ^2[period of ninety days] from the date`
  line `of the decree or order`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 19 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 50 of 2003, s. 5, for period of thirty days (w.e.f. 23-12-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (38601)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 35
  title `Enforcement of decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38601&sectionno=28A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `[28A. Enforcement of decrees and orders--All decrees and orders made by the court in any`
  line `proceeding under this Act shall be enforced in the like manner as the decrees and orders of the court made`
  line `in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction for the time being in forced.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38602)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 36
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992&sectionId=38602&sectionno=29&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00004_195525_1517807318992
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A marriage solemnized between Hindus before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `which is otherwise valid, shall not be deemed to be invalid or ever to have been invalid by reason only of`
  line `the fact that the parties thereto belonged to the same gotra or pravara or belonged to different religions,`
  line `castes or sub-divisions of the same caste.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Act shall be deemed to affect any right recognised by custom or`
  line `conferred by any special enactment to obtain the dissolution of a Hindu marriage, whether solemnized`
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this Act shall affect any proceeding under any law for the time being in`
  line `force for declaring any marriage to be null and void or for annulling or dissolving any marriage or for`
  line `judicial separation pending at the commencement of this Act, and any such proceeding may be continued`
  line `and determined as if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this Act shall be deemed to affect the provisions contained in the Special`
  line `Marriage Act, 1954, (43 of 1954) with respect to marriages between Hindus solemnized under that Act,`
  line `whether before or after the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
